# Knowledge Base Conventions

Rules for the LLM Knowledge Base plugin ecosystem. All KB skills must follow these conventions.

## Directory Layout

```
knowledge-bases/                    # Root for all KBs
└── {topic-slug}/                   # One directory per topic
    ├── manifest.json               # Metadata, source registry, stats
    ├── raw/                        # Ingested source material (human + LLM curated)
    │   ├── {slug}.md               # Converted markdown sources
    │   ├── {slug}.pdf              # Binary originals
    │   └── assets/                 # Downloaded images/media
    │       └── {slug}/             # Per-source asset folder
    ├── wiki/                       # LLM-compiled wiki (LLM-owned, rarely human-edited)
    │   ├── _index.md               # Master index with article summaries
    │   ├── _summary.md             # Executive summary (~500-1000 words)
    │   ├── _concept-map.md         # Mermaid concept relationship diagram
    │   ├── _glossary.md            # Key terms and definitions
    │   ├── concepts/               # Core concept articles
    │   ├── references/             # Per-source reference notes
    │   ├── connections/            # Cross-concept synthesis articles
    │   ├── queries/                # Filed Q&A answers (auto file-back)
    │   ├── outputs/                # Filed output artifacts (auto file-back)
    │   └── images/                 # Generated diagrams
    └── outputs/                    # Generated artifacts
        ├── slides/                 # Marp slide decks
        ├── charts/                 # Matplotlib visualizations
        ├── reports/                # Research reports
        ├── diagrams/               # Mermaid/visual diagrams
        ├── explainers/             # HTML visual explainers
        └── auto-builder/           # Automation logs and reports
```

## Naming Conventions

- **Topic slugs**: lowercase, hyphens, no spaces (e.g., `transformer-architectures`)
- **File slugs**: derived from title, lowercase, hyphens, max 60 chars
- **Index files**: prefixed with `_` (e.g., `_index.md`, `_summary.md`)
- **Wiki articles**: plain `.md` files with YAML frontmatter

## Frontmatter Requirements

Every wiki article MUST have YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Article Title"
category: "concepts|references|connections|queries|outputs"
related: ["other-concept-1", "other-concept-2"]
sources: ["raw/source-file.md"]
last_compiled: "YYYY-MM-DD"
word_count: 850
---
```

Every raw source MUST have:

```yaml
---
title: "Source Title"
source: "https://original-url"
source_type: "web-article|arxiv-paper|youtube|github-repo|pdf|markdown|text"
author: "Author Name"
date_published: "YYYY-MM-DD"
date_ingested: "YYYY-MM-DD"
tags: []
word_count: 1234
summary: "One-line summary"
---
```

## Cross-Reference Syntax

- Wiki-style links for internal references: `[[concept-name]]`
- Relative paths for raw sources: `[title](../raw/source.md)`
- Mermaid for diagrams: fenced code blocks with `mermaid` language

## LLM Ownership Principle

The wiki/ directory is **owned by the LLM**. Humans contribute raw sources to raw/; the LLM compiles, maintains, and enhances the wiki. Manual edits are discouraged except for corrections. After manual edits, run kb-index to refresh indexes.

## Manifest Schema

`manifest.json` is the single source of truth for KB metadata:

```json
{
  "topic": "topic-slug",
  "created": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "description": "Brief topic description",
  "sources": [
    {
      "slug": "source-slug",
      "title": "Source Title",
      "source_url": "https://...",
      "source_type": "web-article",
      "date_ingested": "YYYY-MM-DD",
      "file": "raw/source-slug.md",
      "word_count": 1234
    }
  ],
  "stats": {
    "raw_count": 15,
    "wiki_articles": 28,
    "total_words": 42000,
    "last_compiled": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "concepts": 18,
    "references": 15,
    "connections": 5
  }
}
```

## Incremental Compilation Rules

- New raw sources trigger incremental compilation (update, don't overwrite)
- Never delete existing wiki articles during incremental compilation
- Regenerate all `_` prefixed index files after any wiki change
- Update `manifest.json` stats after every operation

## Output Conventions

- Marp slides: YAML front matter with `marp: true`
- Matplotlib: save as PNG at 150 DPI
- Reports: markdown with optional DOCX conversion
- All outputs reference the KB topic and generation date

## Obsidian Compatibility

Wiki articles are designed to be viewable in Obsidian:
- `[[wikilinks]]` are Obsidian-compatible
- Image paths use relative references
- Marp slides viewable with the Obsidian Marp plugin
- Mermaid diagrams render natively in Obsidian

## Automation Configuration

The `manifest.json` supports an `automation` section for continuous KB construction:

```json
{
  "automation": {
    "watch_dirs": ["~/ObsidianVault/Clippings/", "knowledge-bases/{topic}/inbox/"],
    "feeds": [
      {
        "url": "https://arxiv.org/rss/cs.AI",
        "filter": "transformer|attention",
        "max_items": 5,
        "last_fetched": "2026-04-03"
      }
    ],
    "enhance": {
      "depth": "light",
      "auto_file_back": true
    },
    "last_auto_run": "2026-04-03T14:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

### Automation Rules

- **Watch dirs**: new files are copied to `raw/` and trigger `kb-ingest → kb-compile (incremental) → kb-index`
- **Feed subscriptions**: fetched entries are saved as markdown stubs in `raw/`, then processed through the ingest pipeline
- **Auto file-back**: query answers and generated outputs are automatically archived into `wiki/queries/` and `wiki/outputs/` respectively; use `--no-file-back` to opt out
- **Enhancement cycle**: `kb-lint → auto-fix → kb-compile (incremental) → kb-index`; runs on `enhance` or `full-auto` mode with configurable depth (`light` = stale/incomplete only, `deep` = full wiki)
- **CLI wrapper**: `scripts/kb_cli.py` provides standalone automation (init, watch, feed, add) without the Cursor IDE

### Output Directory for Auto-Builder

```
knowledge-bases/{topic}/outputs/auto-builder/
├── {timestamp}-watch-log.md      # Watch batch processing log
├── {timestamp}-feed-log.md       # Feed fetch processing log
└── {timestamp}-enhance-report.md # Enhancement cycle report
```

## Skill Invocation Order

For full pipeline: `kb-ingest → kb-compile → kb-index → kb-lint → kb-output`
For quick add: `kb-ingest → kb-compile (incremental) → kb-index`
For enhancement: `kb-lint → fix → kb-compile (incremental) → kb-index`
For automation: `kb-auto-builder (watch|feed|enhance|full-auto)` → delegates to appropriate skills
For file-back: query/output results → auto-save to `wiki/queries/` or `wiki/outputs/` → `kb-index`
